%N A390469 Array read by ascending antidiagonals: A(n,k) = [x^n] (1 - x^k)/(1 - 2*x + x^(1+k)), with k >= 0.
%C A390469 A(n,k) is the number of possible outcome sequences of length n of fair coin flips that do not contain k consecutive heads.
%D A390469 Miklos Bona, Introduction to Enumerative and Analytic Combinatorics, CRC Press, 2025, pp. 391-392.
%e A390469 The array begins as:
%e A390469   0, 1,  1,  1,   1,   1,   1, ...
%e A390469   0, 1,  2,  2,   2,   2,   2, ...
%e A390469   0, 1,  3,  4,   4,   4,   4, ...
%e A390469   0, 1,  5,  7,   8,   8,   8, ...
%e A390469   0, 1,  8, 13,  15,  16,  16, ...
%e A390469   0, 1, 13, 24,  29,  31,  32, ...
%e A390469   0, 1, 21, 44,  56,  61,  63, ...
%e A390469   0, 1, 34, 81, 108, 120, 125, ...
%e A390469   ...
%t A390469 A[n_,k_]:=SeriesCoefficient[(1-x^k)/(1-2x+x^(1+k)),{x,0,n}]; Table[A[n-k,k],{n,0,12},{k,0,n}]//Flatten
%Y A390469 Columns k=0..16 give: A000004, A000012, A000045, A000073, A000078, A001591, A001592, A066178, A079262, A104144, A122265, A168082, A168083, A168084, A220469, A220493, A249169.
%Y A390469 Main diagonal gives A000225.
%Y A390469 Rows n=0..2 give: A057427, A130130, A113311.
%Y A390469 Antidiagonal sums give A048888.
